---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="About | Wet Dog Drones"
  description="Meet Michael Lilley, founder of Wet Dog Drones. 12 years in drones, 5 years commercially licensed. Part 107 certified construction documentation specialist in Colorado.">

  <section class="bg-slate-900 text-white py-20">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6">About Wet Dog Drones</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-slate-300">A one-person operation that punches above its weight.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">The Story</h2>
        
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-6">
          Wet Dog Drones started with a $7,000 personal loan and a dream that turned out to be harder than expected. I bought a drone and a GNSS receiver, got my Part 107, and waited for the money to roll in.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-6">
          Spoiler: It didn't.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-6">
          The first three years were a grind. Working weekends. Answering emails at 1 AM. Building relationships one project at a time. The "Part 107 = license to print money" narrative sold by drone training courses? That's a lie. The money is out there, but you've got to chase it. You've got to show up. And you've got to be willing to grind.
        </p>

        <blockquote class="bg-slate-100 border-l-4 border-blue-600 p-6 my-8 text-xl italic">
          "I'm not a traditional drone service provider. I'm embedded in your workflow, not an outside vendor. When I use my day job's truck to get to site, I don't charge mileage. That's how this works."
        </blockquote>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 mt-12">The Numbers</h2>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
          <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-blue-600">12</div>
            <div class="text-slate-600">Years in drones</div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-blue-600">5</div>
            <div class="text-slate-600">Years commercially licensed (Part 107)</div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-blue-600">3</div>
            <div class="text-slate-600">Years grinding before consistent revenue</div>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-blue-600">6</div>
            <div class="text-slate-600">Days/week schedule (1 AM starts)</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 mt-12">The Philosophy</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-6">
          Construction documentation isn't about pretty pictures. It's about protecting your project from the disputes that always come. Every project over $5M needs baseline documentation before the first shovel hits dirt. When the change orders come — and they will — you need proof of what was actually there.
        </p>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-6">
          I've been on both sides of the fence. I understand how construction projects actually work because I'm embedded in them. I know what superintendents need, what VDC teams require, and what holds up in a dispute.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 mt-12">Certifications & Equipment</h2>

        <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg text-slate-600">
          <li>✓ FAA Part 107 Remote Pilot Certificate</li>
          <li>✓ Class D Airspace Authorization (when required)</li>
          <li>✓ RTK/PPK GNSS for high-precision accuracy</li>
          <li>✓ Insurance: Commercial drone liability coverage</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 mt-12">Why "Wet Dog Drones"?</h2>

        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-6">
          Because the dog comes to work with me. Because construction sites are muddy. And because "professional drone services" sounds like everyone else. We're not everyone else.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-20 bg-slate-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 text-center max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Ready to Work Together?</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-8">
        Let's talk about your project and how documentation can protect your budget.
      </p>
      <a href="/contact" class="bg-blue-600 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-blue-700 transition text-lg inline-block">
        Get in Touch
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
